<br>
I'm writing a scipt for an animation I'm going to create called, &quot;Complete Misery&quot;. Any GOOD pointers to get me started?<br>
<br>
GothicSketches <p>//--//--GOTHICSKETCHES--\\--\\</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thehawk>The Hawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/21/02 7:34:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Little Help...</span><hr size=1> I'm not pro but I can still help.<br>
<br>
First of all, you have the title right? So, what's the genre of your animation? Is it a drama? Comedy?<br>
<br>
The type of character you're going to use depends a lot in this. You cannot have a drama with little and cute Chibi characters!!. I really don't know how to help you more if you don't give me a little spoiler of your work.<br>
<br>
BUT, if it is an Animation, then you should take the tutorial of PolyKarbon oriented to Storyboards.<br>
<br>
I know it wasn't a great help, but it's a start. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicsketches.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GothicSketches</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.salon.com/books/feature/1999/08/05/goth/goth.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/21/02 7:58:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.salon.com/books/feature/1999/08/05/goth/goth.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Little Help...</span><hr size=1> Hawk-<br>
<br>
The genre of this series is sort of a strange one, Gothic/Action/Drama...don't ask. It's not with cute little chibi characters either...infact the three main characters are at least 18...Carmine is the main character<br>
<br>
GothicSketches <p>[img]http://www.salon.com/books/feature/1999/08/05/goth/goth.jpg[/img]
//--//--GOTHICSKETCHES--\\--\\</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thehawk>The Hawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/21/02 9:03:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Little Help...</span><hr size=1> You got me wrong, but whatever...<br>
<br>
Gothic/Action/Drama eh? I must say that's weird man. I guess that you're referring to monsters, goth people with painted nails and stuff like that, right? If not, I'm sorry.<br>
<br>
It also depends in what kind of Animation you want. is it going to be Anime(Japanese style) or more like the comic stuff seen in PolyKarbon?. If you plan to create an Anime story, then you should get Flash 5. I've heard that's the best tool for Animation out there. Just check out Animetion.com, the owner haves a couple of good clips there.<br>
<br>
If you choose something more realistic, then you should get POSER 5(Pretty expensive) and give it a try. You can get these programs in eBay with a significant discount(Poser 5 in $15 dollars, do I need to say more?). Please notice that POSER isn't a design tool, you get the characters, then you give them some clothes and start the fun; so there isn't an actual creative effort at all.<br>
<br>
First of all, you should start drawing the main characters out of your imagination(You just can't start animating without a storyboard) to give them some personality.<br>
<br>
That's just an start... oh, one more thing.<br>
<br>
HAVE FUN!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicsketches.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GothicSketches</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.salon.com/books/feature/1999/08/05/goth/goth.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/21/02 9:10:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.salon.com/books/feature/1999/08/05/goth/goth.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Little Help...</span><hr size=1> Hawk-<br>
